name: Psychology Department Organization of Graduate Students
description:
The purpose of PDOGS shall be to promote collaboration among graduate students in the Psychology Department at Texas A&M, and to facilitate the relationship between the Psychology Department and graduate students.

The major goals of PDOGS shall be

1) to encourage collaborative relationships and a community among graduate students in the Psychology Department,

2) to assist open dialogue between the Psychology Department and graduate students, and

3) to raise funds to support social and research activities to enhance collaboration among graduate students.
summary: The purpose of PDOGS shall be to promote collaboration among graduate students in the Psychology Department at Texas A&M, and to facilitate the relationship between the Psychology Department and graduate students.
